---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import JournalSubNav from '../../components/JournalSubNav.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Best British Schools in Bangkok — Journal" description="A guide to Bangkok's top-ranked British curriculum schools, covering fees, UK affiliations, and what parents should know.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <JournalSubNav active="Cities" />

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="relative w-full h-[60vh] min-h-[400px] overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/bangkok-hero.jpg"
      alt="Bangkok skyline at dusk"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/30 to-transparent"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-6 md:p-12">
      <div class="bsa-container max-w-2xl">
        <p class="label text-white/70 mb-4">Cities</p>
        <h1 class="text-white text-3xl md:text-5xl leading-tight">Best British Schools in Bangkok</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="font-body text-black/50 text-sm mb-8">Updated April 2026 &middot; 5 min read</p>

      <div class="space-y-6 font-body text-black/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Bangkok has seven British curriculum schools in the British Schools Asia index — one of the deepest markets in Southeast Asia. The city blends UK-branded campuses (Shrewsbury, Wellington, Brighton, Harrow) with long-established independents (Bangkok Patana, St Andrews, Denla British).
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/shrewsbury-international-school-bangkok">Shrewsbury International School Bangkok</a> leads the city ranking. Founded in 2003, Shrewsbury operates a Riverside campus on the Chao Phraya for senior years (with boarding) and a City Campus in Huai Khwang for primary. The school runs the English National Curriculum through to IGCSE and A Levels.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/wellington-college-international-school-bangkok">Wellington College International School Bangkok</a>, ranked second, opened in 2018 on a 10-acre campus in Krungthep Kreetha. <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/brighton-college-bangkok">Brighton College Bangkok</a> and <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/harrow-international-school-bangkok">Harrow International School Bangkok</a> sit at #3 and #4 respectively. Harrow Bangkok offers boarding from Year 6 — one of the few Bangkok schools to do so.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/denla-british-school">Denla British School</a> in Nonthaburi, on the western edge of greater Bangkok, runs an enhanced English National Curriculum with specialist subject teaching. Headmaster Jonny Liddell is a Cambridge graduate with NPQH qualifications. Accreditations include CIS, COBIS, Cambridge International, and ONESQA.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/bangkok-patana-school">Bangkok Patana School</a> deserves a separate note. Founded in 1957, Patana is the longest-running British international school in Thailand and anchors the Bang Na expat community on La Salle Road. With approximately 2,300 students it is also one of the largest. The pathway is ENC through IGCSE to the IB Diploma — so families committed to A Levels should look elsewhere. Bangkok Patana ranks sixth in our fee-led index, but it remains the heritage choice for many long-term Bangkok families.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/schools/thailand/bangkok/st-andrews-international-school-bangkok">St Andrews International School Bangkok</a> (1997, Cognita group) sits at the more accessible end of the index, running ENC + IGCSE then the IB Diploma in sixth form.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">Fees in context</h2>

        <p>
          Bangkok's British schools cluster between USD 18,900 and USD 25,900 per year for Year 3 — substantially lower than Singapore (USD 33,000+ at the top schools) or Hong Kong, and far below mainland China where premium fees can exceed USD 47,000. Combined with Bangkok's lower cost of living, the city offers strong value for families seeking a British education.
        </p>

        <p>
          Most schools charge tuition only at the headline fee. Registration, exam fees, school trips, and uniform are typically extra. Some schools (notably Harrow) also charge capital or development levies — confirm before committing.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4">What parents should know</h2>

        <p>
          UK-school branding varies in depth. All five UK-branded schools carry the name of a well-known British institution, but the operational connection differs. Some maintain close curriculum oversight, teacher exchange, and quality assurance; others operate more independently under a licensing arrangement. Patana, St Andrews and Denla are independent of any UK parent.
        </p>

        <p>
          Post-16 pathway is the second decision. Shrewsbury, Harrow, Brighton, Wellington and Denla all offer A Levels. Bangkok Patana runs the IB Diploma only. St Andrews offers the IB Diploma. If you are committed to one pathway, the choice narrows quickly.
        </p>

        <p>
          Bangkok traffic is the third. Sukhumvit-corridor families have St Andrews and Patana within reach; Krungthep Kreetha suits Wellington and Brighton; Nonthaburi families have Denla. Cross-Bangkok daily commutes are punishing.
        </p>

        <p>
          For a full breakdown of every school, visit the <a href="/cities/bangkok">Bangkok city page</a> or browse the <a href="/rankings">full rankings</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <hr class="divider container-narrow" />

  <!-- RELATED -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="label mb-6">Related</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
        <a href="/rankings" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          Asia's Top British Schools — Full Rankings
        </a>
        <a href="/cities/bangkok" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          Bangkok City Guide
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="font-display text-xl no-underline hover:underline" style="text-decoration:none;">
          How We Rank Schools
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
